{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016gwnAtxDYDghNHPpaFqgwy","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 0.5.1: Stream-JSON Claude Driver\n     2→\n     3→Status: review\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As an operator,\n     8→I want ralph's Claude driver to use stream-json output format,\n     9→so that tool calls and text are available in real time instead of buffered until exit.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→1. **Given** the claude-code driver (`ralph/drivers/claude-code.sh`), **When** it builds the command, **Then** it uses `--output-format stream-json --verbose --include-partial-messages` instead of `--output-format json`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→2. **Given** stream-json output, **When** Claude runs, **Then** stdout produces NDJSON (one JSON object per line) during execution — not 0 bytes until exit. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→3. **Given** the driver change, **When** the final result is needed, **Then** the last line with `type: \"result\"` contains session_id, cost, result text. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→4. **Given** stream-json piped through ralph, **When** an iteration completes, **Then** ralph detects success/failure/timeout from the output. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→\n    18→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    19→\n    20→- [x] Task 1: Change `driver_build_command()` to use stream-json (AC: #1)\n    21→  - [x] In `ralph/drivers/claude-code.sh`, replace the `CLAUDE_OUTPUT_FORMAT` check block (lines 83-85) so it always emits `--output-format stream-json --verbose --include-partial-messages` instead of conditionally emitting `--output-format json`\n    22→  - [x] Remove or update the `CLAUDE_OUTPUT_FORMAT` env var handling — the driver now always uses stream-json\n    23→  - [x] Remove the `driver_prepare_live_command()` function (lines 127-148) — it is now redundant since the base command already uses stream-json\n    24→- [x] Task 2: Update `CLAUDE_OUTPUT_FORMAT` default in ralph.sh (AC: #1, #2)\n    25→  - [x] In `ralph/ralph.sh` line 50, change `CLAUDE_OUTPUT_FORMAT=\"${CLAUDE_OUTPUT_FORMAT:-json}\"` to `CLAUDE_OUTPUT_FORMAT=\"${CLAUDE_OUTPUT_FORMAT:-stream-json}\"`\n    26→  - [x] In `src/commands/run.ts` line 213-215, update the env block that sets `CLAUDE_OUTPUT_FORMAT = 'json'` — this should now set `stream-json` (or be removed if run.ts should not override the default)\n    27→- [x] Task 3: Update `execute_iteration()` result extraction for NDJSON (AC: #3, #4)\n    28→  - [x] The output file now contains NDJSON (many lines) instead of one JSON blob\n    29→  - [x] After Claude exits with code 0, extract the result from the LAST line matching `\"type\".*\"result\"` using: `grep '\"type\"' \"$output_file\" | grep '\"result\"' | tail -1`\n    30→  - [x] The error-detection grep at line 785 still works on NDJSON since it greps through the full file — verify it doesn't false-positive on stream event lines\n    31→  - [x] The API limit detection grep at line 828 and transient error grep at line 832 should still work — they grep the full output file for error strings\n    32→  - [x] The `wc -c` output size check at line 791 still works — NDJSON is larger than buffered JSON, so this is fine\n    33→- [x] Task 4: Update live output mode for NDJSON (AC: #2)\n    34→  - [x] In the `LIVE_OUTPUT == true` branch (line 709-720), the `tee` pipeline already writes all output to both the terminal and the output file — this works unchanged with NDJSON\n    35→  - [x] Consider piping through the existing `driver_stream_filter()` jq filter (lines 151-166) for terminal display during live mode, so the operator sees formatted tool/text events instead of raw JSON\n    36→  - [x] For background mode (line 722-754), the monitoring loop polling `sprint-state.json` continues to work — output file grows during execution instead of being empty\n    37→- [x] Task 5: Write BATS integration tests (AC: #1, #3, #4)\n    38→  - [x] Test that `driver_build_command` produces args containing `--output-format stream-json --verbose --include-partial-messages`\n    39→  - [x] Test that `driver_build_command` does NOT produce `--output-format json`\n    40→  - [x] Test extracting the result line from a mock NDJSON output file\n    41→  - [x] Test that error detection greps work correctly against NDJSON content (no false positives from stream event type fields)\n    42→\n    43→## Dev Notes\n    44→\n    45→### Current State — What Exists\n    46→\n    47→**Epic 0 (done)** established:\n    48→- Story 0.1: `sprint-state.json` live updates during execution\n    49→- Story 0.2: Ralph polls `sprint-state.json` and displays structured progress\n    50→- Story 0.3: `DashboardFormatter` in `src/lib/dashboard-formatter.ts` reformats ralph output for the `codeharness run` terminal\n    51→\n    52→**The driver already has stream-json infrastructure** (partially built):\n    53→- `driver_supports_live_output()` returns 0 (true) — line 122-124\n    54→- `driver_prepare_live_command()` exists (lines 127-148) — it clones `CLAUDE_CMD_ARGS`, swaps `json` for `stream-json`, and appends `--verbose --include-partial-messages`\n    55→- `driver_stream_filter()` exists (lines 151-166) — a jq filter that extracts text deltas and tool starts from stream events\n    56→\n    57→**The problem:** `driver_build_command()` still builds the command with `--output-format json` by default. The live command builder is a separate function that was never integrated into the main flow. This story makes stream-json the default and only format.\n    58→\n    59→### Key Files to Modify\n    60→\n    61→- `ralph/drivers/claude-code.sh` — Change `driver_build_command()` to always use stream-json. Remove `driver_prepare_live_command()` (redundant). Keep `driver_stream_filter()` (used for terminal display).\n    62→- `ralph/ralph.sh` — Change `CLAUDE_OUTPUT_FORMAT` default. Update `execute_iteration()` result extraction to handle NDJSON.\n    63→- `src/commands/run.ts` — Update `CLAUDE_OUTPUT_FORMAT` env var value from `'json'` to `'stream-json'` in the JSON output mode block (lines 213-215).\n    64→\n    65→### Key Files to Read (do NOT modify)\n    66→\n    67→- `_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/research/technical-stream-json-terminal-rendering-research-2026-03-19.md` — stream-json event format reference\n    68→- `src/lib/dashboard-formatter.ts` — Understands ralph's `[LEVEL] message` output format. NOT changed in this story.\n    69→- `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/0-3-run-command-dashboard.md` — predecessor story context\n    70→\n    71→### stream-json Event Format (Quick Reference)\n    72→\n    73→Each stdout line is a JSON object. Key event types:\n    74→\n    75→| Wrapper type | Inner event type | What it means |\n    76→|:------------|:----------------|:-------------|\n    77→| `stream_event` | `content_block_start` (tool_use) | Tool call starting (has `.event.content_block.name`) |\n    78→| `stream_event` | `content_block_delta` (text_delta) | Text streaming (has `.event.delta.text`) |\n    79→| `stream_event` | `content_block_delta` (input_json_delta) | Tool input streaming |\n    80→| `stream_event` | `content_block_stop` | Content block complete |\n    81→| `stream_event` | `message_start` / `message_stop` | Message lifecycle |\n    82→| `result` | — | Final result with `session_id`, `cost_usd`, `result` text |\n    83→\n    84→The `result` event is always the LAST line. It contains the same data that the old `--output-format json` mode returned as a single blob.\n    85→\n    86→### NDJSON Result Extraction\n    87→\n    88→Old approach (json mode):\n    89→```bash\n    90→# output_file contains one JSON object\n    91→jq '.result' \"$output_file\"\n    92→```\n    93→\n    94→New approach (stream-json mode):\n    95→```bash\n    96→# output_file contains many NDJSON lines, result is the last one\n    97→tail -1 \"$output_file\"\n    98→# Or more defensively:\n    99→grep '\"type\"' \"$output_file\" | grep '\"result\"' | tail -1\n   100→```\n   101→\n   102→### Critical Constraint: Ralph's Error Detection\n   103→\n   104→Ralph's `execute_iteration()` greps the output file for error patterns (lines 785-838). These greps scan the entire file, which now contains NDJSON. Key concern:\n   105→\n   106→- `grep -qi \"5.*hour.*limit\"` — safe, these strings don't appear in stream events\n   107→- `grep -qi \"Internal server error\\|api_error\\|overloaded\"` — safe, stream events don't contain these strings\n   108→- `grep -v '\"[^\"]*error[^\"]*\":' | grep -qE '(^Error:|^ERROR:)'` — the `-v` filter excludes lines with JSON error keys, and the second grep looks for lines STARTING with \"Error:\" — NDJSON lines start with `{`, so this is safe\n   109→\n   110→No changes needed to error detection logic.\n   111→\n   112→### What This Story Does NOT Include\n   113→\n   114→- No changes to `DashboardFormatter` — that reads ralph's `[LEVEL]` lines, not Claude's NDJSON\n   115→- No terminal rendering of stream events — that's Story 0.5.3 (Ink renderer)\n   116→- No stream event parsing module — that's Story 0.5.2 (Stream Event Parser)\n   117→- No changes to `sprint-state.json` format or writing\n   118→\n   119→### Architecture Decision: stream-json as Default\n   120→\n   121→After this story, ALL Claude invocations through ralph use stream-json. There is no fallback to json mode. Rationale:\n   122→- stream-json output is a superset — the result event contains everything json mode returned\n   123→- The output file is slightly larger (many lines vs one blob) but this doesn't matter for logs\n   124→- Future stories (0.5.2, 0.5.3, 0.5.4) depend on stream-json being the default\n   125→\n   126→### Project Structure Notes\n   127→\n   128→- Driver files live in `ralph/drivers/` — one file per platform driver\n   129→- Ralph core is `ralph/ralph.sh` with helper libs in `ralph/lib/`\n   130→- Tests for ralph are BATS tests in `ralph/tests/` (if they exist) or can be added\n   131→- TypeScript run command is `src/commands/run.ts`\n   132→\n   133→### References\n   134→\n   135→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-operational-excellence.md#Story 0.5.1] — acceptance criteria and user story\n   136→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/research/technical-stream-json-terminal-rendering-research-2026-03-19.md] — stream-json format, event types, implementation options\n   137→- [Source: ralph/drivers/claude-code.sh] — current driver with existing stream-json infrastructure (lines 121-166)\n   138→- [Source: ralph/ralph.sh#execute_iteration] — iteration execution, output handling, error detection (lines 653-840)\n   139→- [Source: src/commands/run.ts] — run command, env var setup, DashboardFormatter integration\n   140→- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/0-3-run-command-dashboard.md] — predecessor story, DashboardFormatter design\n   141→\n   142→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   143→## Verification Requirements\n   144→\n   145→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/0-5-1-stream-json-claude-driver.proof.md`)\n   146→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   147→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n   148→\n   149→## Documentation Requirements\n   150→\n   151→- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (list modules touched)\n   152→- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/0-5-1-stream-json-claude-driver.md`\n   153→\n   154→## Testing Requirements\n   155→\n   156→- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   157→- [ ] Integration tests for cross-module interactions\n   158→- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n   159→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   160→\n   161→## Dev Agent Record\n   162→\n   163→### Agent Model Used\n   164→\n   165→Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n   166→\n   167→### Debug Log References\n   168→\n   169→N/A\n   170→\n   171→### Completion Notes List\n   172→\n   173→- Changed driver to always use `--output-format stream-json --verbose --include-partial-messages`\n   174→- Removed `driver_prepare_live_command()` — redundant now that base command uses stream-json\n   175→- Updated `CLAUDE_OUTPUT_FORMAT` default from `json` to `stream-json` in ralph.sh\n   176→- Updated `run.ts` to set `stream-json` instead of `json` in env\n   177→- Verified error detection greps in `execute_iteration()` work correctly with NDJSON (no false positives)\n   178→- Live output tee pipeline works unchanged — NDJSON flows through\n   179→- Background mode monitoring works unchanged — output file grows during execution\n   180→- 28 BATS tests pass (including 8 new NDJSON-specific tests)\n   181→- 32 TypeScript tests pass (including updated env var assertion)\n   182→\n   183→### File List\n   184→\n   185→- `ralph/drivers/claude-code.sh` — driver_build_command uses stream-json, removed driver_prepare_live_command\n   186→- `ralph/ralph.sh` — CLAUDE_OUTPUT_FORMAT default changed to stream-json\n   187→- `src/commands/run.ts` — env var set to stream-json\n   188→- `tests/driver_claude_code.bats` — updated + 8 new NDJSON tests\n   189→- `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` — updated env assertion\n   190→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01UKKB3PMobBy3PqEkAuMMiW","session_id":"14bb9049-f41e-41a8-aff7-919131cd9a0b","uuid":"d5945dee-5269-4223-8dbf-a7dbec37769a","timestamp":"2026-03-21T10:36:50.700Z"}
