{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015jJvMkj6rpgm4YVkwYfkwQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 0.5.4: Run Command Integration\n     2→\n     3→Status: verifying\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As an operator,\n     8→I want `codeharness run` to use the Ink renderer by default with full stream-json piping,\n     9→so that I see live Claude activity (tool calls, text thoughts, story progress) during execution.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→1. **Given** `codeharness run` starts, **When** Claude uses stream-json output, **Then** the Ink renderer shows live tool/text activity (tool starts with spinner, completed tools, text thoughts). <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→\n    15→2. **Given** the old DashboardFormatter existed for ralph output parsing, **When** the Ink renderer is active, **Then** the same information (story completions, failures, sprint progress) is displayed plus deeper tool/text visibility — DashboardFormatter is no longer used in the run command's live output path. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→\n    17→3. **Given** ralph reads Claude stdout as NDJSON, **When** output is piped through the run command, **Then** each line is parsed via `parseStreamLine()` and fed to the Ink renderer via `rendererHandle.update()`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→\n    19→4. **Given** `--quiet` flag, **When** `codeharness run` starts, **Then** no Ink renderer is started, no terminal output is produced. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→\n    21→5. **Given** a `result` event at the end of a Claude session, **When** ralph processes it, **Then** the same data (session_id, cost, result text) is extracted for status updates as before the stream-json switch. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→\n    23→6. **Given** sprint-state.json updates during execution, **When** the polling interval fires, **Then** the Ink header refreshes with current story key, phase, done/total counts, and elapsed time. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    24→\n    25→7. **Given** sprint-status.yaml contains per-story statuses, **When** the renderer is active, **Then** the story breakdown section shows stories grouped by status with UX spec symbols (done/in-progress/pending/failed/blocked). <!-- verification: integration-required -->\n    26→\n    27→8. **Given** ralph logs a story completion or failure, **When** the event is detected, **Then** the Ink renderer displays a story message ([OK]/[WARN]/[FAIL]) with details. <!-- verification: integration-required -->\n    28→\n    29→9. **Given** process exit (SIGINT, SIGTERM, or natural end), **When** the run command terminates, **Then** the Ink renderer is cleaned up (no orphaned terminal state), the polling interval is cleared, and the exit code is propagated correctly. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    30→\n    31→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    32→\n    33→- [x] Task 1: Verify existing stream-json → Ink pipeline in run.ts (AC: #1, #3)\n    34→  - [x] Confirm `run.ts` already imports `parseStreamLine` and `startRenderer`\n    35→  - [x] Confirm `makeLineHandler()` correctly buffers partial lines, parses via `parseStreamLine()`, and feeds events to `rendererHandle.update()`\n    36→  - [x] Confirm both `child.stdout` and `child.stderr` are piped through the handler\n    37→  - [x] Write unit test verifying the line handler parses NDJSON lines and calls `update()` for each recognized event\n    38→\n    39→- [x] Task 2: Add elapsed time to sprint state polling (AC: #6)\n    40→  - [x] Track session start time (`Date.now()` at spawn) in `run.ts`\n    41→  - [x] In the sprint state polling interval, compute elapsed and format as \"Xm\" or \"XhYm\"\n    42→  - [x] Pass `elapsed` field in `SprintInfo` to `rendererHandle.updateSprintState()`\n    43→  - [x] Write unit test for elapsed time formatting\n    44→\n    45→- [x] Task 3: Feed per-story statuses to Ink renderer (AC: #7)\n    46→  - [x] In the sprint state polling interval, read sprint-status.yaml via `readSprintStatus()`\n    47→  - [x] Map story statuses to `StoryStatusEntry[]` — map `done` → `done`, `in-progress`/`review`/`verifying` → `in-progress`, `backlog`/`ready-for-dev` → `pending`\n    48→  - [x] Call `rendererHandle.updateStories(entries)` on each poll cycle\n    49→  - [x] Write unit test for status mapping logic\n    50→\n    51→- [x] Task 4: Detect story completion/failure from ralph output and emit messages (AC: #8)\n    52→  - [x] Parse ralph's `[SUCCESS] Story {key}: DONE` lines from stderr and call `rendererHandle.addMessage({ type: 'ok', key, message: '...' })`\n    53→  - [x] Parse ralph's `[ERROR]` / `[WARN] Story {key} exceeded retry limit` lines and call `rendererHandle.addMessage({ type: 'fail' | 'warn', ... })`\n    54→  - [x] Decide: parse from stderr (ralph structured output) vs. from sprint-state.json polling\n    55→  - [x] Write unit test for message extraction from ralph output lines\n    56→\n    57→- [x] Task 5: Remove or deprecate DashboardFormatter usage in run command (AC: #2)\n    58→  - [x] Verify `run.ts` no longer imports or uses `DashboardFormatter`\n    59→  - [x] If `DashboardFormatter` is still imported, remove the import and any related code\n    60→  - [x] Do NOT delete `dashboard-formatter.ts` — it may be used by other consumers\n    61→  - [x] Write test confirming DashboardFormatter is not referenced in run.ts\n    62→\n    63→- [x] Task 6: Verify quiet mode (AC: #4)\n    64→  - [x] Confirm `startRenderer({ quiet: true })` returns no-op handle\n    65→  - [x] Confirm `spawn` uses `stdio: 'ignore'` when quiet\n    66→  - [x] Write test for quiet mode behavior\n    67→\n    68→- [x] Task 7: Verify result event extraction (AC: #5)\n    69→  - [x] Confirm ralph's `execute_iteration()` extracts the result from the last NDJSON line with `type: \"result\"`\n    70→  - [x] Confirm `run.ts` reads `ralph/status.json` on exit and produces correct JSON output\n    71→  - [x] Write test for result extraction from NDJSON\n    72→\n    73→- [x] Task 8: Verify cleanup on exit (AC: #9)\n    74→  - [x] Confirm `rendererHandle.cleanup()` is called on both `child.on('close')` and `child.on('error')`\n    75→  - [x] Confirm `sprintStateInterval` is cleared on exit\n    76→  - [x] Confirm exit code is propagated to `process.exitCode`\n    77→  - [x] Write test for cleanup behavior (mock child process)\n    78→\n    79→## Dev Notes\n    80→\n    81→### Current State — What Exists\n    82→\n    83→**Stories 0.5.1–0.5.3 (done/verifying)** established:\n    84→- 0.5.1: Ralph driver uses `--output-format stream-json --verbose --include-partial-messages`\n    85→- 0.5.2: `parseStreamLine()` in `src/lib/stream-parser.ts` converts NDJSON → typed `StreamEvent`\n    86→- 0.5.3: Ink renderer in `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` with `App`, `Header`, `StoryBreakdown`, `StoryMessages`, tool display, and all controller methods\n    87→\n    88→**run.ts is already ~80% integrated.** The current `src/commands/run.ts`:\n    89→- Already imports `parseStreamLine` and `startRenderer`\n    90→- Already buffers stdout/stderr lines and pipes through `parseStreamLine()` → `rendererHandle.update()`\n    91→- Already polls sprint-state.json every 5 seconds and calls `rendererHandle.updateSprintState()`\n    92→- Already handles quiet mode, cleanup on close/error, exit code propagation\n    93→- Does NOT yet pass `elapsed` time to the sprint info\n    94→- Does NOT yet feed per-story statuses via `updateStories()`\n    95→- Does NOT yet emit story messages via `addMessage()`\n    96→\n    97→### Key Files to Modify\n    98→\n    99→- `src/commands/run.ts` — Add elapsed time tracking, per-story status feeding, story message detection from ralph output\n   100→- `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` — Add tests for new integration behavior\n   101→\n   102→### Key Files to Read (Do NOT Modify)\n   103→\n   104→- `src/lib/stream-parser.ts` — StreamEvent types and `parseStreamLine()`\n   105→- `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` — `RendererHandle` interface with `update()`, `updateSprintState()`, `updateStories()`, `addMessage()`\n   106→- `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` — `SprintInfo`, `StoryStatusEntry`, `StoryMessage` types\n   107→- `src/lib/dashboard-formatter.ts` — Legacy formatter, verify it's no longer used in run.ts\n   108→- `src/lib/beads-sync.ts` — `readSprintStatus()` for reading sprint-status.yaml\n   109→- `ralph/ralph.sh` — Ralph's structured output format (`[SUCCESS]`, `[ERROR]`, `[WARN]` lines on stderr)\n   110→\n   111→### Integration Points\n   112→\n   113→1. **Stream-JSON pipeline (already wired):** `child.stdout` → `makeLineHandler()` → `parseStreamLine()` → `rendererHandle.update(event)`. This is working. Verify, don't rewrite.\n   114→\n   115→2. **Sprint state polling (needs enhancement):** The 5-second interval already reads `sprint-state.json` and updates the header. Enhance with:\n   116→   - Elapsed time computation from session start\n   117→   - Per-story status from `readSprintStatus()` → `updateStories()`\n   118→\n   119→3. **Ralph stderr → story messages (new):** Ralph's stderr contains structured `[LEVEL] message` lines. Parse these in the stderr line handler to detect story completions/failures and call `addMessage()`.\n   120→\n   121→### Ralph Output Patterns (from DashboardFormatter)\n   122→\n   123→Key patterns to detect for story messages:\n   124→- `[SUCCESS] Story {key}: DONE` → `addMessage({ type: 'ok', key, message: 'DONE — ...'})`\n   125→- `[WARN] Story {key} exceeded retry limit` → `addMessage({ type: 'fail', key, message: 'exceeded retry limit' })`\n   126→- `[WARN] Story {key} — retry N/M` → `addMessage({ type: 'warn', key, message: 'retry N/M' })`\n   127→- `[ERROR] ...` → optionally surface as warn/fail messages\n   128→\n   129→### Elapsed Time Formatting\n   130→\n   131→Use the same format as the UX spec: \"47m\", \"2h14m\". The `formatElapsed()` in `dashboard-formatter.ts` produces \"Xm Ys\" which is slightly different. Create an inline helper or reuse/adapt.\n   132→\n   133→### Status Mapping\n   134→\n   135→Sprint-status.yaml values → StoryStatusValue:\n   136→- `done` → `done`\n   137→- `in-progress`, `review`, `verifying` → `in-progress`\n   138→- `backlog`, `ready-for-dev` → `pending`\n   139→- `failed` → `failed`\n   140→- `blocked`, `exhausted` → `blocked`\n   141→\n   142→### What This Story Does NOT Include\n   143→\n   144→- No changes to `ink-renderer.tsx` or `ink-components.tsx` — those are complete from 0.5.3\n   145→- No changes to `stream-parser.ts` — complete from 0.5.2\n   146→- No changes to ralph scripts — driver change complete from 0.5.1\n   147→- No new Ink components — this story USES existing components\n   148→- No DashboardFormatter deletion — it may still be referenced by tests or other consumers\n   149→\n   150→### Architecture Constraints\n   151→\n   152→- **NFR9: No file > 300 lines.** `run.ts` is currently 358 lines. If integration code pushes it further, extract helpers to a separate file (e.g., `src/lib/run-helpers.ts` or `src/lib/ralph-output.ts`).\n   153→- **Vitest** for unit tests, **100% coverage target**\n   154→- Do NOT introduce new npm dependencies\n   155→\n   156→### References\n   157→\n   158→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-operational-excellence.md#Story 0.5.4] — original epic ACs\n   159→- [Source: src/commands/run.ts] — current integration (already ~80% wired)\n   160→- [Source: src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx] — RendererHandle API\n   161→- [Source: src/lib/ink-components.tsx] — component types (SprintInfo, StoryStatusEntry, StoryMessage)\n   162→- [Source: src/lib/stream-parser.ts] — StreamEvent types and parser\n   163→- [Source: src/lib/dashboard-formatter.ts] — legacy formatter patterns for ralph output\n   164→- [Source: src/lib/beads-sync.ts] — readSprintStatus() for sprint-status.yaml\n   165→\n   166→## Dev Agent Record\n   167→\n   168→### Implementation Plan\n   169→\n   170→- Extracted `countStories`, `buildSpawnArgs`, `formatElapsed`, `mapSprintStatus`, `mapSprintStatuses`, and `parseRalphMessage` into `src/lib/run-helpers.ts` to comply with NFR9 (300-line max). `run.ts` re-exports `countStories` and `buildSpawnArgs` for backward compatibility.\n   171→- Added `sessionStartTime` tracking at spawn time; elapsed is formatted as \"Xm\"/\"XhYm\" and passed to `SprintInfo.elapsed`.\n   172→- Added initial and polling-interval calls to `readSprintStatus()` → `mapSprintStatuses()` → `rendererHandle.updateStories()`.\n   173→- Added `parseRalph: true` option to stderr line handler so ralph `[SUCCESS]`/`[WARN]`/`[ERROR]` lines are parsed into `StoryMessage` objects and fed to `rendererHandle.addMessage()`.\n   174→- Decision: ralph message parsing is done from stderr (ralph structured output), not from sprint-state.json polling. This gives immediate feedback.\n   175→\n   176→### Completion Notes\n   177→\n   178→All 8 tasks completed. 86 new/updated tests across 2 test files. Full regression suite passes (2728 tests, 0 failures). `run.ts` reduced from 358 to 300 lines. No new npm dependencies.\n   179→\n   180→## File List\n   181→\n   182→- `src/commands/run.ts` — Modified: added elapsed time, story status feeding, ralph message parsing; extracted helpers\n   183→- `src/lib/run-helpers.ts` — New: extracted helpers (formatElapsed, mapSprintStatus, mapSprintStatuses, parseRalphMessage, countStories, buildSpawnArgs)\n   184→- `src/lib/__tests__/run-helpers.test.ts` — New: 43 unit tests for all helper functions\n   185→- `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` — Modified: added tests for elapsed time (AC #6), per-story statuses (AC #7), story messages (AC #8), DashboardFormatter absence (AC #2); added updateStories/addMessage mocks\n   186→- `src/lib/AGENTS.md` — Modified (review): added run-helpers.ts documentation entry\n   187→\n   188→## Senior Developer Review (AI)\n   189→\n   190→**Reviewer:** ivintik (AI-assisted) — 2026-03-20\n   191→\n   192→### Issues Found: 1 HIGH, 3 MEDIUM, 1 LOW\n   193→\n   194→**HIGH:**\n   195→1. **AGENTS.md missing for new module** — `run-helpers.ts` (new file in `src/lib/`) was not documented in `src/lib/AGENTS.md`. **FIXED:** Added entry under new \"Run Command Helpers\" category.\n   196→\n   197→**MEDIUM:**\n   198→2. **Duplicate test code** — `countStories` and `buildSpawnArgs` had identical tests in both `run-helpers.test.ts` and `run.test.ts`. **FIXED:** Replaced `run.test.ts` duplicates with minimal re-export verification tests. Canonical tests remain in `run-helpers.test.ts`.\n   199→3. **Polling interval code untested** — The `setInterval` callback in `run.ts` (lines 207-228) was never exercised by tests, leaving AC #6 (elapsed time refresh) and AC #7 (per-story status refresh) only tested for the initial call. **FIXED:** Added polling interval test using `vi.useFakeTimers()`.\n   200→4. **Missing Showboat proof document** — No `docs/exec-plans/active/0-5-4-run-command-integration.proof.md`. **NOT FIXED:** deferred to verification phase (showboat is generated during verification, not review).\n   201→\n   202→**LOW:**\n   203→5. **Misleading test name** — Test `--max-story-retries defaults to 3` actually asserts default is `'10'`. **FIXED:** Renamed to `--max-story-retries defaults to 10`.\n   204→\n   205→### AC Validation\n   206→\n   207→| AC | Status | Evidence |\n   208→|----|--------|----------|\n   209→| #1 Stream-JSON → Ink pipeline | IMPLEMENTED | `run.ts` lines 180-204, tested in `run.test.ts` \"Ink renderer integration\" |\n   210→| #2 DashboardFormatter removed | IMPLEMENTED | No DashboardFormatter import in `run.ts`, tested |\n   211→| #3 NDJSON parsing via parseStreamLine | IMPLEMENTED | `run.ts` lines 189-191, tested |\n   212→| #4 --quiet mode | IMPLEMENTED | `run.ts` lines 144-145, 172, tested |\n   213→| #5 Result event extraction | IMPLEMENTED | `run.ts` lines 246-288, tested |\n   214→| #6 Elapsed time in polling | IMPLEMENTED | `run.ts` lines 147, 159, 217, tested (initial + interval) |\n   215→| #7 Per-story statuses | IMPLEMENTED | `run.ts` lines 165-169, 222-224, tested (initial + interval) |\n   216→| #8 Story messages from ralph | IMPLEMENTED | `run.ts` lines 194-199, tested |\n   217→| #9 Cleanup on exit | IMPLEMENTED | `run.ts` lines 232-242, tested |\n   218→\n   219→### Coverage\n   220→\n   221→- `run.ts`: 95.52% statements, 70.23% branches, 100% functions\n   222→- `run-helpers.ts`: 98.63% statements, 95.83% branches, 100% functions\n   223→- Overall: 96.65% (target: 90%)\n   224→- Per-file floor: all 111 files above 80%\n   225→\n   226→### Outcome: APPROVED — all HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed. Status → verifying.\n   227→\n   228→## Change Log\n   229→\n   230→- 2026-03-20: Story 0-5-4 implemented — run command now passes elapsed time, per-story statuses, and ralph story messages to Ink renderer; DashboardFormatter confirmed unused; helpers extracted to run-helpers.ts for NFR9 compliance.\n   231→- 2026-03-20: Code review — fixed AGENTS.md gap, duplicate tests, missing polling interval test, misleading test name. Status → verifying.\n   232→\n   233→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   234→## Verification Requirements\n   235→\n   236→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/0-5-4-run-command-integration.proof.md`)\n   237→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   238→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n   239→\n   240→## Documentation Requirements\n   241→\n   242→- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (list modules touched)\n   243→- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/0-5-4-run-command-integration.md`\n   244→\n   245→## Testing Requirements\n   246→\n   247→- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   248→- [ ] Integration tests for cross-module interactions\n   249→- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n   250→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   251→"}]}