{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UKKB3PMobBy3PqEkAuMMiW","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The retrospective is written and updated at `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/epic-0-5-retrospective.md`.\n\n**Summary of findings:**\n\nEpic 0.5 was a well-executed four-story pipeline epic. The layered decomposition (transport, parsing, rendering, integration) was clean, stories were independently testable, and the code review process caught real issues. The main friction was in verification of story 0-5-2, where a missing export, ESM container workarounds, and a verify tool presentation bug created disproportionate overhead for what was a simple pure function.\n\nKey action items: fix the `codeharness verify` presentation bug (reports FAIL on 6/6 pass), add an integration test for package entry point exports, tag stories with `verification-tier` at planning time, and enforce sprint change proposals for scope additions (Epic 0.5 was injected by a subagent without authorization).\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Epic-level problems:**\n\n- **Verification ceremony disproportionate to code complexity.** Story 0-5-2 is a ~50-line pure function with comprehensive unit tests, yet verification required: fixing an export gap, working around ESM/CLI side effects in the container, dealing with a verify tool bug, and overriding a pre-commit gate. Two commits were needed. This pattern will recur for every pure-function library story.\n- **Story status inconsistency is a recurring pattern.** Status mismatches between sprint-status.yaml and story files appeared in 0-5-2 (showed `verified`, not a valid status) and 0-5-3 (showed `verifying` in file, `done` in sprint status). No validation exists on the status field.\n- **Session issues log incomplete.** Entries exist for 0-5-1 and 0-5-2 but not 0-5-3 or 0-5-4. This created data gaps for the retrospective.\n\n**Stories harder than expected:**\n\n- **0-5-2 (Stream Event Parser):** Hardest to verify despite being the simplest code. Root causes: not exported from package entry point, container ESM friction, verify tool presentation bug. The implementation itself was trivial.\n- **0-5-4 (Run Command Integration):** Required extracting helpers to a new file to meet NFR9. Not harder than expected, but the code review found 5 issues including an untested polling interval — the most issues of any story in the epic.\n\n**Action items — immediate attention:**\n\n1. **A1: Fix `codeharness verify` presentation bug** — reports FAIL when all ACs pass. This affects every future verification run.\n2. **A7: Add integration test for package entry point exports** — the 0-5-2 export gap would have been caught by a test importing from `dist/`.\n\n**Action items — backlog:**\n\n3. A2: Tag stories with verification-tier at planning time\n4. A3: E2E test for stream-JSON pipeline\n5. A4: Enforce sprint change proposals for scope additions\n6. A5: Automate story status synchronization\n7. A8: Split entry point into library + CLI bootstrap\n\n**Process improvements to encode in tooling/config:**\n\n- The `verification-tier` tag (`<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->`) should be **required** in story templates, not optional. The create-story workflow should prompt for it.\n- The verify tool's FAIL/PASS determination should be based on AC pass rate only, not on ancillary checks (missing proof doc, metadata issues).\n- Package entry point export coverage should be a CI check, not a manual verification step."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: adb1c92b439f7d9ba (use SendMessage with to: 'adb1c92b439f7d9ba' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 44733\ntool_uses: 23\nduration_ms: 180844</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"14bb9049-f41e-41a8-aff7-919131cd9a0b","uuid":"bcfe2751-1484-4add-9812-7abfa91c06bd","timestamp":"2026-03-21T10:39:36.827Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /retrospective for Epic 0.5 (Stream-JSON Live Activity Display). All 4 stories are complete:\n- 0-5-1-stream-json-claude-driver: done\n- 0-5-2-stream-event-parser: done\n- 0-5-3-ink-terminal-renderer: done\n- 0-5-4-run-command-integration: done\n\nRead the sprint status at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml and the session issues log at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md for context.\n\nReview the epic's work, extract lessons learned, and produce the retrospective document.\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/epic-0-5-retrospective.md.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Epic-level problems (recurring patterns across stories, process breakdowns)\n- Stories that were harder than expected and why\n- Action items that need immediate attention vs. backlog\n- Process improvements that should be encoded in tooling/config, not just documented\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"adb1c92b439f7d9ba","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The retrospective is written and updated at `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/epic-0-5-retrospective.md`.\n\n**Summary of findings:**\n\nEpic 0.5 was a well-executed four-story pipeline epic. The layered decomposition (transport, parsing, rendering, integration) was clean, stories were independently testable, and the code review process caught real issues. The main friction was in verification of story 0-5-2, where a missing export, ESM container workarounds, and a verify tool presentation bug created disproportionate overhead for what was a simple pure function.\n\nKey action items: fix the `codeharness verify` presentation bug (reports FAIL on 6/6 pass), add an integration test for package entry point exports, tag stories with `verification-tier` at planning time, and enforce sprint change proposals for scope additions (Epic 0.5 was injected by a subagent without authorization).\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Epic-level problems:**\n\n- **Verification ceremony disproportionate to code complexity.** Story 0-5-2 is a ~50-line pure function with comprehensive unit tests, yet verification required: fixing an export gap, working around ESM/CLI side effects in the container, dealing with a verify tool bug, and overriding a pre-commit gate. Two commits were needed. This pattern will recur for every pure-function library story.\n- **Story status inconsistency is a recurring pattern.** Status mismatches between sprint-status.yaml and story files appeared in 0-5-2 (showed `verified`, not a valid status) and 0-5-3 (showed `verifying` in file, `done` in sprint status). No validation exists on the status field.\n- **Session issues log incomplete.** Entries exist for 0-5-1 and 0-5-2 but not 0-5-3 or 0-5-4. This created data gaps for the retrospective.\n\n**Stories harder than expected:**\n\n- **0-5-2 (Stream Event Parser):** Hardest to verify despite being the simplest code. Root causes: not exported from package entry point, container ESM friction, verify tool presentation bug. The implementation itself was trivial.\n- **0-5-4 (Run Command Integration):** Required extracting helpers to a new file to meet NFR9. Not harder than expected, but the code review found 5 issues including an untested polling interval — the most issues of any story in the epic.\n\n**Action items — immediate attention:**\n\n1. **A1: Fix `codeharness verify` presentation bug** — reports FAIL when all ACs pass. This affects every future verification run.\n2. **A7: Add integration test for package entry point exports** — the 0-5-2 export gap would have been caught by a test importing from `dist/`.\n\n**Action items — backlog:**\n\n3. A2: Tag stories with verification-tier at planning time\n4. A3: E2E test for stream-JSON pipeline\n5. A4: Enforce sprint change proposals for scope additions\n6. A5: Automate story status synchronization\n7. A8: Split entry point into library + CLI bootstrap\n\n**Process improvements to encode in tooling/config:**\n\n- The `verification-tier` tag (`<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->`) should be **required** in story templates, not optional. The create-story workflow should prompt for it.\n- The verify tool's FAIL/PASS determination should be based on AC pass rate only, not on ancillary checks (missing proof doc, metadata issues).\n- Package entry point export coverage should be a CI check, not a manual verification step."}],"totalDurationMs":180844,"totalTokens":44733,"totalToolUseCount":23,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":597,"cache_read_input_tokens":43282,"output_tokens":853,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":597},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
