{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Gb3kqoKCyC42aGXZB4RNus","type":"tool_result","content":"   210→- [ ] Add structured log events for audit/onboard CLI interactions (observability gap noted during 3-3 verification)\n   211→- [ ] Improve `dfGap()` branch coverage from 87.5% to 100% — cosmetic but keeps the bar clean\n   212→\n   213→---\n   214→\n   215→# Session Retrospective — 2026-03-21 (end-of-day consolidation)\n   216→\n   217→**Timestamp:** ~09:20Z\n   218→**Sprint progress:** 17/20 stories done (85%), Epic 3 complete (released as v0.23.1), Epic 4 blocked on 4-1 re-verification\n   219→**Releases this session:** v0.23.0 (Epic 0.5 dashboard), v0.23.1 (Epic 3 audit command)\n   220→\n   221→---\n   222→\n   223→## 1. Session Summary\n   224→\n   225→| Story | Epic | Final Status | Phases Completed Today | Notes |\n   226→|-------|------|-------------|----------------------|-------|\n   227→| 3-3-onboard-alias | Epic 3: Audit Command | Done | verify | All 8 ACs passed. Epic 3 closed. Released in v0.23.1. |\n   228→| 4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation | Epic 4: Infrastructure | Verifying | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verify (partial) | 9/10 ACs passed. AC10 failed, bug fixed, awaiting re-verification. |\n   229→\n   230→**Full-day throughput:** 2 stories progressed, 1 completed and released, 1 epic closed, 2 releases shipped.\n   231→\n   232→**Test suite at session end:** 2820 tests passing across 120 files, ~97% overall coverage, all files above 80% floor.\n   233→\n   234→---\n   235→\n   236→## 2. Issues Analysis\n   237→\n   238→### Bugs Discovered (cumulative, all sessions today)\n   239→\n   240→| Severity | Story | Issue | Resolution |\n   241→|----------|-------|-------|------------|\n   242→| HIGH | 3-3 | Unsafe double type assertion (`as unknown as Record`) | Fixed: spread operator |\n   243→| HIGH | 4-1 | Operator precedence ambiguity in `checkVerificationTools` | Fixed: added parentheses |\n   244→| MEDIUM | 3-3 | Dead branch guard (`fixStories &&` always true) | Fixed: simplified to `else` |\n   245→| MEDIUM | 4-1 | `checkNoSourceCopy` missed `COPY --chown` patterns | Fixed: regex updated |\n   246→| MEDIUM | 4-1 | Redundant double-read of Dockerfile | Fixed: removed duplicate read |\n   247→| MEDIUM | 4-1 | Missing test for `COPY --from=` binary install pattern | Fixed: test added |\n   248→| **MEDIUM** | **4-1** | **AC10: `validateDockerfile()` warnings not propagated to audit output** | **Fixed: warning-to-gap propagation added in dimensions.ts. Needs re-verification.** |\n   249→| LOW | 3-3 | Branch coverage gap — `skipped: true` path untested | Fixed: test added, 100% branch coverage |\n   250→\n   251→**Bug discovery rate:** 8 bugs across 2 stories — 4 per story average. Code review caught 6 of 8 (75%). Verification caught 1 (AC10 propagation). Pre-implementation analysis caught 1 (dead branch).\n   252→\n   253→### Workarounds / Tech Debt Introduced This Session\n   254→\n   255→1. **`console.log` in audit-action.ts** — Needs `raw()` output utility. Not fixed.\n   256→2. **`formatAuditJson()` is a no-op** — Exists for symmetry. Not fixed.\n   257→3. **Loose tool matching in `checkVerificationTools`** — `content.includes(tool)` matches anywhere. Accepted by design.\n   258→4. **`checkBinaryOnPath` missing line numbers** — Inconsistent with other checks. Not fixed.\n   259→5. **Broken BATS tests skipped** — `fix: skip broken onboard BATS tests that block CI` (commit b5f062c). Tests were skipped rather than fixed to unblock the release. **This is real tech debt.**\n   260→\n   261→### Verification Gaps\n   262→\n   263→- **4-1 AC10 re-verification pending** — Bug was found and fixed, but the story needs a clean verification pass to confirm the fix works end-to-end.\n   264→- **Observability gap** — No structured log events for audit/onboard CLI interactions. Pre-existing, not introduced this session.\n   265→\n   266→### Tooling/Infrastructure Problems\n   267→\n   268→- **Pre-existing `run-helpers.test.ts` failure** — `--live` flag test was broken before this session. Had to be fixed ad-hoc during 3-3 verification. Wasted time.\n   269→- **BATS test breakage** — Onboard BATS integration tests broke after the onboard-to-audit refactor. Rather than fixing them, they were skipped (commit b5f062c) to unblock CI for the release. The skipped tests need to be updated to match the new onboard-as-alias behavior.\n   270→\n   271→---\n   272→\n   273→## 3. What Went Well\n   274→\n   275→- **Epic 3 fully completed and released.** Three stories (3-1, 3-2, 3-3) all done, verified, committed, and shipped as v0.23.1. Clean epic closure.\n   276→- **Two releases shipped in one session.** v0.23.0 (dashboard) and v0.23.1 (audit command) both released without pipeline failures.\n   277→- **Code review consistently catches real bugs.** 6 of 8 bugs found during code review across both stories. The review gate is the highest-value quality check in the pipeline.\n   278→- **Session issues log worked as designed.** Every subagent phase (create-story, dev-story, code-review, verify) contributed entries. The log provided complete raw materials for this retrospective without requiring any file archaeology.\n   279→- **Shared handler pattern successful.** The `audit-action.ts` extraction reduced 478 lines to 40 lines while maintaining identical behavior. Clean, testable, reusable.\n   280→- **Test suite growth healthy.** 2783 to 2820 tests (+37), one new coverage-tracked file, coverage held at ~97%.\n   281→\n   282→---\n   283→\n   284→## 4. What Went Wrong\n   285→\n   286→- **4-1 verification discovered a real integration bug (AC10).** `validateDockerfile()` warnings were stored in the result but never propagated through `checkInfrastructure()` to the audit output. This is an integration seam that unit tests missed — the validator worked, the coordinator worked, but the wiring between them dropped warnings.\n   287→- **BATS tests skipped instead of fixed.** Commit b5f062c skips broken onboard BATS tests to unblock CI. This is a shortcut that reduces integration test coverage. The tests need updating, not skipping.\n   288→- **Full pipeline doesn't fit in one window for non-trivial stories.** Both stories required multiple session windows to complete create-dev-review-verify. Story 4-1 still hasn't completed verification after two windows.\n   289→- **Pre-existing broken tests wasted time.** The `--live` flag test failure in `run-helpers.test.ts` was unrelated to any current work but blocked 3-3 verification.\n   290→- **Test file size estimates remain unreliable.** Story 3-3 estimated 100-150 lines for `onboard.test.ts`; actual was 325 (compacted to 230). This pattern repeats across sprints.\n   291→\n   292→---\n   293→\n   294→## 5. Lessons Learned\n   295→\n   296→### Patterns to Repeat\n   297→\n   298→- **Code review as mandatory gate.** Two stories, 6 bugs caught before merge. Non-negotiable.\n   299→- **Session issues log as retrospective source material.** Every subagent writes to it. The retro just categorizes and synthesizes.\n   300→- **AC expansion during story creation.** Going from 4 epic-level ACs to 10 story-level ACs gave granular verification targets. Do this for every story.\n   301→- **Shared handler extraction for command aliases.** The `audit-action.ts` pattern eliminates code duplication cleanly. Use this whenever two commands share behavior.\n   302→\n   303→### Patterns to Avoid\n   304→\n   305→- **Skipping tests to unblock releases.** Fix the tests or mark them as `TODO` with a tracking issue. Skipping silently erodes coverage.\n   306→- **Trusting unit tests alone for integration seams.** The AC10 bug (warnings not propagated) existed because the validator and coordinator were tested in isolation. Integration tests or end-to-end tests are needed at module boundaries.\n   307→- **Carrying broken tests forward.** If a test is broken, fix it immediately or it will block something else later.\n   308→- **Estimating test sizes at story planning time.** The estimates are consistently 50-100% low. Stop estimating test LOC; estimate test case count instead.\n   309→\n   310→---\n   311→\n   312→## 6. Action Items\n   313→\n   314→### Fix Now (Before Next Session)\n   315→\n   316→- [ ] Complete re-verification of 4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation (AC10 fix needs clean verification pass)\n   317→- [ ] Fix or properly rewrite the skipped BATS onboard tests (commit b5f062c) — they should test the new alias behavior, not be skipped\n   318→\n   319→### Fix Soon (Next Sprint)\n   320→\n   321→- [ ] Add `raw()` output utility to `src/lib/output.ts` — resolves `console.log` tech debt in `audit-action.ts`\n   322→- [ ] Add line number reporting to `checkBinaryOnPath`\n   323→- [ ] Document known false positive scenarios for `checkVerificationTools`\n   324→- [ ] Investigate why `run-helpers.test.ts` `--live` flag test was broken without CI catching it\n   325→- [ ] Add integration test for `checkInfrastructure()` -> `validateDockerfile()` warning propagation path (the seam where AC10 bug lived)\n   326→\n   327→### Backlog (Track but Not Urgent)\n   328→\n   329→- [ ] Consider data-driven Dockerfile rules (parsed from markdown) instead of hardcoded\n   330→- [ ] Add structured log events for audit/onboard CLI interactions\n   331→- [ ] Improve `dfGap()` branch coverage from 87.5% to 100%\n   332→- [ ] Review whether `formatAuditJson()` should do actual formatting or be removed\n   333→- [ ] Add deprecation warnings for dropped onboard subcommands (`coverage`, `audit`, `epic`)\n   334→- [ ] Replace test LOC estimates with test case count estimates in story templates\n   335→\n   336→---\n   337→\n   338→## End-of-Day Metrics\n   339→\n   340→| Metric | Start of Day | End of Day | Delta |\n   341→|--------|-------------|------------|-------|\n   342→| Stories done | 15 | 17 | +2 |\n   343→| Sprint completion | 75% | 85% | +10% |\n   344→| Epics closed | 3 (0, 0.5, 1, 2) | 4 (+Epic 3) | +1 |\n   345→| Tests passing | ~2783 | 2820 | +37 |\n   346→| Coverage-tracked files | 119 | 120 | +1 |\n   347→| Overall coverage | 96.97% | ~97% | steady |\n   348→| Releases shipped | — | 2 (v0.23.0, v0.23.1) | +2 |\n   349→| Bugs found & fixed | — | 8 | — |\n   350→| Tech debt items added | — | 6 | — |\n   351→| Stories still verifying | — | 1 (4-1) | — |\n   352→\n   353→---\n   354→\n   355→# Session Retrospective — 2026-03-21 (late session)\n   356→\n   357→**Timestamp:** ~09:30Z\n   358→**Sprint progress:** 17/20 stories done (85%), 4-1 marked done in sprint-status.yaml, 4-2 create-story in progress\n   359→**Active automation:** ralph is running, currently starting story 4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration\n   360→\n   361→---\n   362→\n   363→## 1. Session Summary\n   364→\n   365→| Story | Epic | Final Status | Activity This Window | Notes |\n   366→|-------|------|-------------|---------------------|-------|\n   367→| 4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation | Epic 4: Infrastructure | Done (per sprint-status.yaml) | Marked complete | AC10 fix was committed (4f0a376). Re-verification either passed or was accepted. |\n   368→| 4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration | Epic 4: Infrastructure | In Progress | create-story phase starting | Ralph automation initiated story creation. No issues logged yet. |\n   369→\n   370→No new entries were added to `.session-issues.md` since the last retro at ~09:20Z. Ralph is actively running (loop_count: 2, status: running) and has moved to 4-2's create-story phase.\n   371→\n   372→**Test suite:** 2820 tests passing across 120 files, ~97% overall coverage (unchanged from last window).\n   373→\n   374→---\n   375→\n   376→## 2. Issues Analysis\n   377→\n   378→### New Issues Since Last Retro\n   379→\n   380→None. The session issues log has not been updated since the 4-1 verify entry at 05:35Z. All issues from today were already analyzed in the end-of-day consolidation retro.\n   381→\n   382→### State Inconsistency Noted\n   383→\n   384→- `sprint-status.yaml` shows `4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation: done`\n   385→- `sprint-state.json` shows `4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation: in-progress`\n   386→- These are out of sync. The yaml is authoritative per project convention. The sprint-state.json may not have been updated after 4-1 was finalized.\n   387→\n   388→### Outstanding Items From Prior Retros (Still Open)\n   389→\n   390→1. **BATS onboard tests still skipped** (commit b5f062c) -- marked \"Fix Now\" in prior retro, not yet addressed\n   391→2. **4-1 re-verification status unclear** -- sprint-status.yaml says done, but no verification entry in session issues log confirms AC10 re-pass\n   392→3. **6 tech debt items from today** -- none resolved yet (raw() utility, formatAuditJson no-op, loose tool matching, missing line numbers, skipped BATS tests, console.log usage)\n   393→\n   394→---\n   395→\n   396→## 3. What Went Well\n   397→\n   398→- **Story 4-1 completed.** Despite the AC10 failure during first verification, the bug was found, fixed, test added, and the story reached done status. The full pipeline worked as intended -- verification caught an integration seam bug that unit tests missed.\n   399→- **Sprint at 85% completion.** 17 of 20 stories done. Epic 0, 0.5, 1, 2, and 3 all fully closed. Only Epics 4 and 5 remain.\n   400→- **Continuous automation.** Ralph seamlessly transitioned from 4-1 completion to 4-2 story creation without manual intervention.\n   401→- **Session issues log discipline held.** Every subagent phase logged its findings consistently across the entire day.\n   402→\n   403→---\n   404→\n   405→## 4. What Went Wrong\n   406→\n   407→- **\"Fix Now\" items from prior retros remain unfixed.** The skipped BATS tests (b5f062c) were flagged as \"Fix Now\" in the ~05:40Z retro and again in the ~09:20Z consolidation. They are still skipped. This pattern of flagging items as urgent and not acting on them erodes the retro process.\n   408→- **State sync gap.** sprint-state.json and sprint-status.yaml disagree on 4-1 status. This makes it unclear whether 4-1 actually passed re-verification or was just marked done.\n   409→- **No new session issues logged for 4+ hours.** Either nothing happened between ~05:40Z and now (possible if ralph was idle), or subagents stopped logging issues. The gap makes it hard to reconstruct what happened."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01WbghDLFsXiBxMyWVBJH7t1","session_id":"14bb9049-f41e-41a8-aff7-919131cd9a0b","uuid":"c4395bd5-b7fb-42eb-a5ad-2fa954106b87","timestamp":"2026-03-21T10:41:05.086Z"}
