{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HFurVop5X91DZ9CqToyqtf","type":"tool_result","content":"   609→\n   610→---\n   611→\n   612→## Sprint Health Assessment\n   613→\n   614→The sprint is effectively complete at 95% (19/20 stories). The remaining 2 stories (5-1, 5-2) are in Epic 5 (Workflow Integration) and marked as backlog -- they were stretch goals, not committed scope. All committed scope is done.\n   615→\n   616→**Key risk:** 8 tech debt items added today with 0 resolved. The skipped BATS tests have been \"Fix Now\" for 4 retros without action. If this pattern continues, tech debt will compound faster than it can be addressed.\n   617→\n   618→**Recommendation:** Before starting any new feature work, dedicate one session to tech debt resolution -- fix the BATS tests, add the `raw()` utility, reconcile the state files, and close at least 3-4 of the 8 open items.\n   619→\n   620→---\n   621→\n   622→# Session Retrospective -- 2026-03-21 (post-final session)\n   623→\n   624→**Timestamp:** ~06:08Z -- ~06:25Z\n   625→**Sprint progress:** 19/20 stories done (95%), Epic 5 partially complete (5-1 done, 5-2 backlog)\n   626→**Active automation:** ralph running, completed 5-1 full pipeline\n   627→**Commit:** 1db2755 feat: story 5-1-code-review-observability-check\n   628→\n   629→---\n   630→\n   631→## 1. Session Summary\n   632→\n   633→| Story | Epic | Final Status | Phases Completed | Notes |\n   634→|-------|------|-------------|-----------------|-------|\n   635→| 5-1-code-review-observability-check | Epic 5: Workflow Integration | Done | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verify | All 6 ACs passed. Committed (1db2755). |\n   636→\n   637→One story completed through the full pipeline in a single automation run (~17 minutes). This was a lightweight story -- primarily patch-file updates with minimal TypeScript code. The main deliverable is markdown enforcement content for code review patches and Semgrep tooling integration.\n   638→\n   639→**Test suite at session end:** 2855 tests passing across 121 files, 96.98% overall coverage, all files above 80% floor.\n   640→\n   641→---\n   642→\n   643→## 2. Issues Analysis\n   644→\n   645→### Bugs Discovered During Implementation\n   646→\n   647→- **MEDIUM: Review patch missing `--json` flag** -- Semgrep command in the review enforcement patch would produce wrong output format. Fixed during code review.\n   648→- **MEDIUM: Tautological test** -- Semgrep JSON contract test validated a hardcoded mock against itself, proving nothing. Replaced with real `parseSemgrepOutput()` integration test during code review.\n   649→- **MEDIUM: Module-scope `readFileSync`** -- Test file would crash entirely if patch file was missing. Moved to `beforeAll` during code review.\n   650→\n   651→### Workarounds Applied (Tech Debt Introduced)\n   652→\n   653→- **Em dash vs double dash inconsistency** (LOW, not fixed) -- Pre-existing inconsistency between patch files and analyzer.ts. Not introduced this session but noted.\n   654→- **Fragile `ROOT` path resolution** (LOW, not fixed) -- Uses `__dirname` + four `..` segments. Brittle if directory structure changes. Pre-existing pattern.\n   655→\n   656→### Code Quality Concerns\n   657→\n   658→- **ACs #2-#4 depend on LLM agent behavior** -- Unit tests can only verify patch content exists, not that Claude will correctly interpret the enforcement instructions during real code reviews. This is an inherent limitation of testing LLM-driven workflows.\n   659→- **Epic AC naming mismatch** -- Epic references `patches/review/review-enforcement.md` but actual file is `patches/review/enforcement.md`. The epic spec was slightly wrong; implementation used the correct name.\n   660→\n   661→### Verification Gaps\n   662→\n   663→- **ACs #2-#4 verified via patch content + Semgrep tooling** rather than live Claude agent sessions. Claude CLI was not authenticated in the verification Docker container. This is a reasonable proxy but not full integration verification.\n   664→\n   665→### Tooling/Infrastructure Problems\n   666→\n   667→- **CRITICAL: verify-env prepare does NOT copy `patches/` into Docker container.** The container uses the globally installed npm package (v0.23.1) which predates this story's changes. First verification run failed 5/6 ACs because patches were stale. Had to manually `docker cp` updated patches into the container.\n   668→- **This is a systemic issue.** Any story that modifies `patches/` will hit this same problem. The verify-env prepare step or Docker image build needs to include current working-tree patches, not just the published npm version.\n   669→\n   670→### State Sync Issues (Persistent)\n   671→\n   672→- **sprint-state.json shows 5-1 as \"review\"** despite sprint-status.yaml showing \"done\" and the commit existing (1db2755). The sprint-state.json / sprint-status.yaml desync continues unresolved from prior retros.\n   673→\n   674→---\n   675→\n   676→## 3. What Went Well\n   677→\n   678→- **Full pipeline in one automation run.** Story 5-1 went from create-story through verify in ~17 minutes with no manual intervention. Lightweight stories are ideal automation candidates.\n   679→- **Code review caught 3 real bugs.** The missing `--json` flag would have caused Semgrep integration to fail silently. The tautological test was giving false confidence. The module-scope readFileSync was a test fragility time bomb. All three caught before merge.\n   680→- **Clean implementation.** 8 new tests, zero regressions, 2855 total tests passing. No flaky tests introduced.\n   681→- **Sprint at 95% with only stretch goals remaining.** All committed scope is done. Story 5-2 (verification-runtime-integration) remains in backlog as a stretch goal.\n   682→- **Session issues log discipline continues.** All 4 phases logged their findings. The log remains the definitive source of truth for retrospectives.\n   683→\n   684→---\n   685→\n   686→## 4. What Went Wrong\n   687→\n   688→- **Verification environment broken for patch-modifying stories.** The verify-env prepare step does not copy current `patches/` into the Docker container. This caused a full first-pass verification failure (5/6 ACs failed). The manual `docker cp` workaround is fragile and non-reproducible. This was flagged but not fixed.\n   689→- **\"Fix Now\" items continue to accumulate without action.** The skipped BATS tests (commit b5f062c) are now in their fifth consecutive retro as \"Fix Now.\" The sprint-state.json desync is in its third. Neither has been addressed.\n   690→- **ACs testing LLM behavior can only be partially verified.** Story 5-1's ACs #2-#4 fundamentally depend on Claude agent behavior during real review sessions. The verification used content-existence checks as a proxy. There's no way to unit-test \"will the LLM follow these instructions.\"\n   691→- **Tech debt count grew to 10 items with 0 resolved.** Every session adds items; none have been closed.\n   692→\n   693→---\n   694→\n   695→## 5. Lessons Learned\n   696→\n   697→### Patterns to Repeat\n   698→\n   699→- **Lightweight stories complete fast in automation.** When the scope is primarily patch-file content with minimal TypeScript, the full pipeline (create-dev-review-verify) can finish in under 20 minutes. Prioritize splitting large stories to get this benefit.\n   700→- **Code review catches bugs in test code, not just production code.** The tautological test and module-scope readFileSync were both in test files. Review should scrutinize tests as carefully as production code.\n   701→- **Manual `docker cp` as verification workaround.** While fragile, it unblocked verification without waiting for an infrastructure fix. Acceptable as a one-time workaround but must not become habit.\n   702→\n   703→### Patterns to Avoid\n   704→\n   705→- **Modifying `patches/` without updating verify-env prepare.** This will break verification for every future patches story. The infrastructure fix should happen before the next patches story, not after.\n   706→- **Flagging \"Fix Now\" items across 5+ retros.** At this point either fix them or admit they are backlog. The \"Fix Now\" label has lost all meaning.\n   707→- **Writing ACs that require LLM behavior verification.** For stories that configure LLM agent behavior (patches, prompts, enforcement rules), ACs should focus on what can be mechanically verified: file existence, content correctness, tool integration. \"Agent follows instructions\" is not testable.\n   708→\n   709→---\n   710→\n   711→## 6. Action Items\n   712→\n   713→### Fix Now (Before Next Session)\n   714→\n   715→- [ ] **Fix verify-env prepare to copy current `patches/` into Docker container** -- This blocks clean verification for any patches-modifying story. Systemic blocker.\n   716→- [ ] **Fix or reclassify skipped BATS onboard tests** (commit b5f062c) -- Fifth retro flagging this. Either fix them now or move to \"Backlog\" with explicit justification. Calling it \"Fix Now\" and ignoring it is dishonest.\n   717→- [ ] **Reconcile sprint-state.json** -- 5-1 shows \"review\" despite being done and committed. Third retro flagging this.\n   718→\n   719→### Fix Soon (Next Sprint)\n   720→\n   721→- [ ] Add multi-line RUN instruction support to `validateDockerfile()` (carried)\n   722→- [ ] Add `raw()` output utility to `src/lib/output.ts` (carried)\n   723→- [ ] Add init-project integration test for `dockerfile` field in InitResult (carried)\n   724→- [ ] Add line number reporting to `checkBinaryOnPath` (carried)\n   725→- [ ] Document known false positive scenarios for `checkVerificationTools` (carried)\n   726→- [ ] Investigate CI gap for `run-helpers.test.ts` --live flag test (carried)\n   727→- [ ] Add integration test for `checkInfrastructure()` -> `validateDockerfile()` warning propagation seam (carried)\n   728→\n   729→### Backlog (Track but Not Urgent)\n   730→\n   731→- [ ] Consider data-driven Dockerfile rules (parsed from markdown) instead of hardcoded (carried)\n   732→- [ ] Add structured log events for audit/onboard CLI interactions (carried)\n   733→- [ ] Improve `dfGap()` branch coverage from 87.5% to 100% (carried)\n   734→- [ ] Review whether `formatAuditJson()` should be removed as a no-op (carried)\n   735→- [ ] Add deprecation warnings for dropped onboard subcommands (carried)\n   736→- [ ] Replace test LOC estimates with test case count estimates (carried)\n   737→- [ ] Add sync mechanism between sprint-status.yaml and sprint-state.json (carried)\n   738→- [ ] Install showboat in verification Docker container (carried)\n   739→- [ ] Fix fragile `ROOT` path resolution using `__dirname` + four `..` segments\n   740→- [ ] Resolve em dash vs double dash inconsistency between patches and analyzer.ts\n   741→- [ ] Write AC guidelines for LLM-behavior-dependent stories -- focus ACs on mechanically verifiable criteria\n   742→\n   743→---\n   744→\n   745→## Cumulative Day Metrics (Final Update)\n   746→\n   747→| Metric | Start of Day | End of Day | Delta |\n   748→|--------|-------------|------------|-------|\n   749→| Stories done | 15 | 19 | +4 |\n   750→| Sprint completion | 75% | 95% | +20% |\n   751→| Epics closed | 3 (0, 0.5, 1, 2) | 5 (+Epic 3, +Epic 4) | +2 |\n   752→| Tests passing | ~2783 | 2855 | +72 |\n   753→| Coverage-tracked files | 119 | 121 | +2 |\n   754→| Overall coverage | 96.97% | 96.98% | steady |\n   755→| Releases shipped | 0 | 2 (v0.23.0, v0.23.1) | +2 |\n   756→| Bugs found & fixed | 0 | 14 | +14 |\n   757→| Tech debt items added | 0 | 10 | +10 |\n   758→| Tech debt items resolved | 0 | 0 | 0 |\n   759→| Retro \"Fix Now\" items carried over | 0 | 3 | +3 |\n   760→| Stories remaining (backlog) | 5 | 1 (5-2) | -4 |\n   761→\n   762→---\n   763→\n   764→## Sprint Health Assessment (Final)\n   765→\n   766→The sprint is at 95% completion (19/20 stories). Story 5-2 (verification-runtime-integration) remains in backlog as a stretch goal. All committed scope is done. Five epics closed today (0, 0.5, 1, 2, 3, 4). Epic 5 is partially complete with 5-1 done and 5-2 in backlog.\n   767→\n   768→**Throughput:** 4 stories completed, 14 bugs found and fixed, 72 new tests added, 2 releases shipped -- all in a single day. The automation pipeline (ralph) handled 3 of 4 stories end-to-end without manual intervention.\n   769→\n   770→**Critical risk: Tech debt at zero resolution rate.** 10 tech debt items added today, 0 resolved. Three \"Fix Now\" items have survived 3-5 consecutive retros without action. The retro \"Fix Now\" classification has become meaningless. The verify-env patches issue is a genuine blocker for future stories.\n   771→\n   772→**Recommendation: Next session must be a tech debt session.** No new feature stories until at least these are resolved: (1) verify-env patches copying, (2) BATS test fix or reclassification, (3) sprint-state.json reconciliation. Then tackle 2-3 \"Fix Soon\" items. Only after that should story 5-2 be attempted.\n   773→\n   774→---\n   775→\n   776→# Session Retrospective — 2026-03-21 (Loop #4)\n   777→\n   778→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence Sprint\n   779→**Session window:** ~06:27Z – ~06:57Z (approx 30 minutes)\n   780→**Sprint progress:** 19/20 stories done (95%), story 5-2 in `verifying`\n   781→**Loop:** 4 of today's ralph autonomous sessions\n   782→\n   783→---\n   784→\n   785→## 1. Session Summary\n   786→\n   787→| Story | Epic | Entry Status | Exit Status | Phases Completed |\n   788→|-------|------|-------------|-------------|-----------------|\n   789→| 5-2-verification-runtime-integration | Epic 5: Workflow Integration | backlog | verifying | create-story, dev-story, code-review |\n   790→\n   791→One story attempted. Story 5-2 is the last story in the sprint and the last story in Epic 5. It progressed through creation, implementation, and code review within the 30-minute budget. Docker-based verification was not reached — by the time code review completed (~06:45Z), approximately 8 minutes remained, which was insufficient for a full verification cycle (typically 10-15 minutes).\n   792→\n   793→The story itself was lightweight (\"thin story\" per the issues log): most code already existed from Epic 2. The implementation was primarily patch updates and test writing. Both dev and code-review phases reported clean runs with no major issues.\n   794→\n   795→**Test results at session end:** 2872 tests passing across 121 files, 96.98% overall coverage, all files above 80% floor.\n   796→\n   797→---\n   798→\n   799→## 2. Issues Analysis\n   800→\n   801→### Bugs Found & Fixed (3)\n   802→\n   803→| Severity | Issue | Where | Resolution |\n   804→|----------|-------|-------|------------|\n   805→| MEDIUM | VerifyResult type contract test was untyped — no compile-time protection against field removal | code-review | Added explicit type annotation |\n   806→| MEDIUM | Missing `saveRuntimeCoverage` persistence test — AC #5 had no test for file I/O path | code-review | Test added |\n   807→| MEDIUM | Patch hardcoded VictoriaLogs URL without noting configurability, inconsistent with verify-prompt.ts endpoint overrides | code-review | Fixed |\n   808→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01WbghDLFsXiBxMyWVBJH7t1","session_id":"14bb9049-f41e-41a8-aff7-919131cd9a0b","uuid":"0c191ad0-1c81-4272-af35-9f7c2202037b","timestamp":"2026-03-21T10:41:15.940Z"}
