{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JA8ATiwH5MDDdqeLnPb9Q8","type":"tool_result","content":"   808→\n   809→### Tech Debt Identified (Not Fixed) (2)\n   810→\n   811→| Severity | Issue | Notes |\n   812→|----------|-------|-------|\n   813→| LOW | Coverage percentage computation duplicated in test — manually replicates formula instead of calling `computeRuntimeCoverage` | Fragile if formula changes |\n   814→| LOW | No test for `parseObservabilityGaps` with multiple gaps in one AC section | Edge case coverage gap |\n   815→\n   816→### Planning/Ambiguity Issues (2)\n   817→\n   818→- **Ambiguity in epic definition:** Epic AC #2 says \"verify-prompt.ts is updated\" but the template already contains observability instructions from Epic 2. Interpreted as a confirmation/regression-test task. Reasonable interpretation but shows epic ACs can drift as implementation proceeds.\n   819→- **Thin story risk:** Most code existed from Epic 2. Risk of dev agent over-engineering was called out at story creation. Dev agent handled it cleanly — no over-engineering observed.\n   820→\n   821→### Systemic Issues (Carried Over)\n   822→\n   823→- **verify-env patches not copied into Docker container** — Identified in loop #3 (story 5-1), still not fixed. Story 5-2 verification will hit this same issue. This is the most critical blocker for completing the sprint.\n   824→\n   825→---\n   826→\n   827→## 3. What Went Well\n   828→\n   829→- **Clean implementation runs.** Both dev-story and code-review phases reported zero issues on first pass. The dev phase had \"None\" in the issues log — the cleanest implementation of the entire sprint day.\n   830→- **Appropriate scoping.** The story was correctly identified as thin at creation time, and the dev agent did not over-engineer. 16 new tests added, focused on the actual requirements.\n   831→- **Code review caught real issues.** Three MEDIUM-severity bugs found and fixed: untyped contract test, missing persistence test, hardcoded URL. All three would have caused problems in verification or future maintenance.\n   832→- **Sprint nearly complete.** 19/20 stories done, 95% completion. Five epics closed. Only verification of story 5-2 remains.\n   833→- **Test count growth.** Sprint day total: 2783 -> 2872 tests (+89 tests across 4 loops).\n   834→\n   835→---\n   836→\n   837→## 4. What Went Wrong\n   838→\n   839→- **Verification not reached.** The primary gap. Story 5-2 exited code review at ~06:45Z with only ~8 minutes left in the 30-minute budget. Verification requires Docker container setup, patch copying (with the known patches issue), and AC-by-AC checks — 10-15 minutes minimum. The story remains in `verifying`.\n   840→- **Sprint cannot close this session.** Epic 5 and the sprint remain open because of this one unverified story.\n   841→- **verify-env patches issue still unresolved.** This was flagged in loop #3's retro as a \"Fix Now\" item. It was not fixed between loops. When story 5-2 verification is attempted, it will hit this same blocker and require the same manual `docker cp` workaround.\n   842→- **Tech debt accumulation continues.** 2 more LOW items added this loop, bringing the day's total to 12 tech debt items with 0 resolved.\n   843→\n   844→---\n   845→\n   846→## 5. Lessons Learned\n   847→\n   848→### Patterns to Repeat\n   849→\n   850→1. **Thin story identification at creation time works.** Calling out \"this is a thin story\" in the issues log set correct expectations and prevented over-engineering.\n   851→2. **Clean dev runs are achievable.** When the codebase is well-established and the story is well-scoped, zero-issue dev phases happen. Stories later in a sprint benefit from the infrastructure built by earlier stories.\n   852→3. **Code review continues to find real bugs.** 3/3 MEDIUM issues found this loop were genuine defects, not style nits. The review phase earns its time cost.\n   853→\n   854→### Patterns to Avoid\n   855→\n   856→1. **Leaving systemic blockers unfixed between loops.** The verify-env patches issue was identified in loop #3 and could have been fixed in the ~5 minutes between loops. Instead it will cost 5-10 minutes of workaround time again in the next verification attempt.\n   857→2. **Attempting verification with <10 minutes remaining.** Verification consistently takes 10-15 minutes. Budget planning should account for this and either skip verification (leaving story in `review`) or allocate sufficient time.\n   858→3. **Zero tech debt resolution across an entire day.** Four loops, 12 tech debt items accumulated, 0 resolved. The debt resolution rate needs a dedicated session.\n   859→\n   860→---\n   861→\n   862→## 6. Action Items\n   863→\n   864→| Priority | Action | Owner | Status |\n   865→|----------|--------|-------|--------|\n   866→| **Fix Now** | Fix verify-env to copy `patches/` into Docker container | Next session | Carried over from loop #3 |\n   867→| **Fix Now** | Run verification for story 5-2 to close Epic 5 and the sprint | Next session | New |\n   868→| **Fix Soon** | Resolve or reclassify the 3 \"Fix Now\" items that have survived 4+ retros | Next session | Carried over |\n   869→| **Fix Soon** | Dedicate a session to tech debt (12 items at 0% resolution rate) | Next sprint | Carried over |\n   870→| **Track** | Add test for `parseObservabilityGaps` with multiple gaps | Backlog | New |\n   871→| **Track** | Replace duplicated coverage formula in test with `computeRuntimeCoverage` call | Backlog | New |\n   872→\n   873→---\n   874→\n   875→## Cumulative Sprint Day Metrics (Loops 1-4)\n   876→\n   877→| Metric | Start of Day | End of Loop 4 | Delta |\n   878→|--------|-------------|---------------|-------|\n   879→| Sprint completion | 75% (15/20) | 95% (19/20) | +20% |\n   880→| Epics closed | 3 | 5 (3, 4 closed; 5 pending verification) | +2 |\n   881→| Tests passing | ~2783 | 2872 | +89 |\n   882→| Coverage-tracked files | 119 | 121 | +2 |\n   883→| Overall coverage | 96.97% | 96.98% | steady |\n   884→| Releases shipped | 0 | 2 (v0.23.0, v0.23.1) | +2 |\n   885→| Bugs found & fixed | 0 | 17 | +17 |\n   886→| Tech debt items added | 0 | 12 | +12 |\n   887→| Tech debt items resolved | 0 | 0 | 0 |\n   888→| Stories remaining | 5 | 1 (5-2 in verifying) | -4 |\n   889→\n   890→---\n   891→\n   892→## Sprint Health Assessment\n   893→\n   894→The sprint is at 95% completion. Story 5-2 has passed code review and needs only Docker verification to close. The implementation is solid — clean dev run, 3 code review bugs fixed, 2872 tests passing.\n   895→\n   896→**The single blocker is verification.** Once the verify-env patches issue is resolved (or worked around via `docker cp`), story 5-2 verification should take ~15 minutes. If all 6 ACs pass (likely given the clean implementation), Epic 5 closes and the sprint is 100% complete.\n   897→\n   898→**Tech debt remains the elephant in the room.** Four retrospectives today have flagged the same systemic issues. The verify-env patches problem has been manually worked around twice rather than fixed. The recommendation from loop #3 stands: the next session after sprint completion should be dedicated to tech debt resolution before starting any new feature work.\n   899→\n   900→---\n   901→\n   902→# Final Sprint Retrospective — 2026-03-21T10:45Z\n   903→\n   904→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence Sprint\n   905→**Full session window:** ~04:21Z – ~06:57Z (approx 2 hours 36 minutes across 5 ralph loops)\n   906→**Sprint result:** 20/20 stories done — 100% complete. All 5 epics closed.\n   907→\n   908→---\n   909→\n   910→## 1. Session Summary\n   911→\n   912→| Story | Epic | Outcome | Phases | Notes |\n   913→|-------|------|---------|--------|-------|\n   914→| 3-3-onboard-alias | 3: Audit Command | Done | create, dev, review, verify | Replaced 478-line onboard with 40-line alias |\n   915→| 4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation | 4: Infra Guidelines | Done | create, dev, review, verify | 9/10 ACs passed first run; AC10 fix applied |\n   916→| 4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration | 4: Infra Guidelines | Done | create, dev, review, verify | Clean run, all 10 ACs passed |\n   917→| 5-1-code-review-observability-check | 5: Workflow Integration | Done | create, dev, review, verify | Patch infrastructure issue required docker cp workaround |\n   918→| 5-2-verification-runtime-integration | 5: Workflow Integration | Done | create, dev, review, verify | Same infrastructure issue; tree-shaking complication |\n   919→\n   920→**Final metrics:** 2872 tests passing, 121 coverage-tracked files, 96.98% overall coverage, all files above 80% floor.\n   921→\n   922→---\n   923→\n   924→## 2. Issues Analysis\n   925→\n   926→### Bugs Discovered During Implementation or Verification\n   927→\n   928→| Issue | Severity | Story | Status |\n   929→|-------|----------|-------|--------|\n   930→| Unsafe double type assertion (`as unknown as Record<...>`) | HIGH | 3-3 | Fixed (spread operator) |\n   931→| Operator precedence ambiguity in `checkVerificationTools` | HIGH | 4-1 | Fixed (added parens) |\n   932→| Unhandled `writeFileSync` exception violating Result<T> contract | HIGH | 4-2 | Fixed (try/catch) |\n   933→| AC10: `validateDockerfile()` warnings not propagated to audit output | HIGH | 4-1 | Fixed (verify phase) |\n   934→| Review patch missing `--json` flag for Semgrep | MEDIUM | 5-1 | Fixed |\n   935→| `checkNoSourceCopy` missed `COPY --chown` flag patterns | MEDIUM | 4-1 | Fixed |\n   936→| Tautological test (mock validated against itself) | MEDIUM | 5-1 | Fixed |\n   937→| Module-scope `readFileSync` crashes test file if patch missing | MEDIUM | 5-1 | Fixed |\n   938→| `VerifyResult` type contract test was untyped | MEDIUM | 5-2 | Fixed |\n   939→| Patch hardcoded VictoriaLogs URL without configurability note | MEDIUM | 5-2 | Fixed |\n   940→| Dead branch guard (`fixStories &&` always true) | MEDIUM | 3-3 | Fixed |\n   941→| Test mock leak (`clearAllMocks` vs `resetAllMocks`) | MEDIUM | 4-2 | Fixed |\n   942→| Missing `projectDir` validation producing garbage paths | MEDIUM | 4-2 | Fixed |\n   943→| `readPatchFile()` path resolution bug — resolves outside package dir | MEDIUM | 5-2 | NOT FIXED (pre-existing) |\n   944→\n   945→**Total bugs found and fixed this session: 17. One pre-existing bug identified but not fixed.**\n   946→\n   947→### Workarounds Applied (Tech Debt Introduced)\n   948→\n   949→1. **Single-line apt-get in templates** (4-2): Templates use `apt-get install curl jq` instead of multi-line format because `validateDockerfile()` checks lines independently. Validator and template generator are coupled to single-line format.\n   950→2. **docker cp for patches** (5-1, 5-2): Verification container uses globally installed npm v0.23.1 which lacks current patches. Manual `docker cp` required twice. This is a systemic problem for any story modifying `patches/`.\n   951→3. **tsx for tree-shaken exports** (5-2): `verifyPromptTemplate()` is tree-shaken from `dist/index.js` because nothing imports it from CLI entry point. Verified via `tsx` instead.\n   952→4. **Patch content verification as proxy for agent integration** (5-1): ACs #2-#4 verified via patch content + semgrep tooling rather than live Claude agent sessions. Reasonable proxy but not full integration test.\n   953→\n   954→### Code Quality Concerns\n   955→\n   956→- `console.log` in `audit-action.ts` — established codebase pattern but violates \"no console.log\" rule. Needs `raw()` output utility.\n   957→- `formatAuditJson()` is a pass-through no-op — exists for symmetry only.\n   958→- `checkVerificationTools` loose matching — `content.includes(tool)` matches anywhere in file.\n   959→- `checkBinaryOnPath` has no line number — inconsistent with other checks.\n   960→- Coverage percentage computation duplicated in test instead of calling `computeRuntimeCoverage`.\n   961→- Fragile `ROOT` path resolution using `__dirname` + four `..` segments.\n   962→- Em dash vs double dash inconsistency between patch and analyzer.ts.\n   963→\n   964→### Verification Gaps\n   965→\n   966→- **No live Claude agent integration test** for review observability patches (5-1 ACs #2-#4). Unit tests verify patch content exists but not agent interpretation.\n   967→- **init-project.test.ts doesn't assert `dockerfile` field** in InitResult (tests predate story 4-2).\n   968→- **No test for `parseObservabilityGaps` with multiple gaps** in one AC section (5-2).\n   969→- **Regex-based Dockerfile validation may false-positive** on complex multi-stage builds (4-1).\n   970→\n   971→### Tooling/Infrastructure Problems\n   972→\n   973→- **verify-env does not copy `patches/` into Docker container.** This broke two stories and will break any future story that modifies patches. Root cause: container uses globally installed npm package, not local source.\n   974→- **Pre-existing test failure in `run-helpers.test.ts`** (`--live` flag test) had to be fixed before 3-3 verification could proceed — unrelated to that story.\n   975→- **Showboat not installed** — skipped re-verification for 4-2 (warning only).\n   976→\n   977→---\n   978→\n   979→## 3. What Went Well\n   980→\n   981→- **Sprint completed 100%.** All 20 stories across 5 epics done in a single day session.\n   982→- **Code review caught 17 real bugs** across 5 stories — the review phase is pulling its weight.\n   983→- **Test suite grew from ~2783 to 2872** (+89 tests) while maintaining 96.98% coverage.\n   984→- **Clean dev runs on 2 of 5 stories** (5-1, 5-2) — zero issues reported by dev agent.\n   985→- **Story 3-3 achieved 92% code reduction** — 478 lines replaced by 40-line alias.\n   986→- **AC10 bug caught by verification** (4-1) — verify phase working as intended, found a gap the dev and review phases missed.\n   987→- **Autonomous execution worked end-to-end** — ralph ran 5 loops, completed 5 stories, no human intervention needed for implementation.\n   988→\n   989→---\n   990→\n   991→## 4. What Went Wrong\n   992→\n   993→- **verify-env patches issue hit twice** (5-1 and 5-2). Same workaround applied both times. Should have been fixed after the first occurrence.\n   994→- **AC10 failure on 4-1** required a fix during verification — the warning-to-gap propagation was missing from `dimensions.ts`. This was a design gap in the story spec (ACs expanded from 4 to 10 but the integration path wasn't fully specified).\n   995→- **12 tech debt items accumulated, 0 resolved.** Every retrospective this session flagged the same systemic issues. The debt is compounding.\n   996→- **Dual file reads in `checkInfrastructure`** shipped in dev and was caught only by code review — dev agent should have caught the redundancy.\n   997→- **Tree-shaking eliminated a needed export** (5-2) — `verifyPromptTemplate()` not reachable from CLI entry point. This is a build configuration issue that will recur.\n   998→\n   999→---\n  1000→\n  1001→## 5. Lessons Learned\n  1002→\n  1003→### Patterns to Repeat\n  1004→\n  1005→- **4-phase pipeline (create, dev, review, verify) is effective.** Review caught 17 bugs; verify caught 1 more that review missed. Both phases justified their cost.\n  1006→- **Expanding epic ACs to story-level ACs** (4-1: 4->10, 4-2: 3->10) improved coverage and caught integration gaps earlier.\n  1007→- **Clean implementation sessions (5-1, 5-2) correlate with well-scoped stories.** Lightweight patch-focused stories had zero dev issues."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01WbghDLFsXiBxMyWVBJH7t1","session_id":"14bb9049-f41e-41a8-aff7-919131cd9a0b","uuid":"e25089fb-e013-4a47-aa5c-34622f47eb8e","timestamp":"2026-03-21T10:41:19.898Z"}
