{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011wk3cdW8AUX5zAezsyFtYa","type":"tool_result","content":"  1008→\n  1009→### Patterns to Avoid\n  1010→\n  1011→- **Applying the same workaround twice instead of fixing root cause.** The docker cp workaround for patches should have been a permanent fix after story 5-1.\n  1012→- **Validator/template coupling to single-line format** (4-1/4-2). Validator should handle multi-line RUN instructions; templates shouldn't be constrained by validator limitations.\n  1013→- **Skipping init-project integration tests** (4-2 Task 5.2). \"Heavy mocking\" is not a valid reason to skip integration coverage for a new feature.\n  1014→\n  1015→---\n  1016→\n  1017→## 6. Action Items\n  1018→\n  1019→### Fix Now (Before Next Session)\n  1020→\n  1021→1. **Fix verify-env to copy `patches/` into Docker container.** This blocked two stories and will block every future patches-modifying story. File: verify-env prepare script.\n  1022→2. **Fix `readPatchFile()` path resolution bug.** Currently resolves outside package directory from `dist/`. Fallback templates always used instead of real patches.\n  1023→3. **Fix tree-shaking of `verifyPromptTemplate()`.** Either add it to CLI exports or create a separate entry point for skill-consumed functions.\n  1024→\n  1025→### Fix Soon (Next Sprint)\n  1026→\n  1027→4. **Add `raw()` output utility** to replace direct `console.log` in audit-action.ts and other handlers.\n  1028→5. **Make `validateDockerfile()` handle multi-line RUN instructions** (backslash continuations). Current single-line checking produces false negatives.\n  1029→6. **Add init-project.test.ts assertions for `dockerfile` field** in InitResult.\n  1030→7. **Stabilize `ROOT` path resolution** — replace `__dirname` + four `..` segments with a proper root-finding utility.\n  1031→\n  1032→### Backlog (Track But Not Urgent)\n  1033→\n  1034→8. Remove `formatAuditJson()` no-op or give it real formatting logic.\n  1035→9. Add line numbers to `checkBinaryOnPath` for consistency.\n  1036→10. Add test for `parseObservabilityGaps` with multiple gaps in one AC section.\n  1037→11. Resolve em dash vs double dash inconsistency between patch and analyzer.ts.\n  1038→12. Investigate false positive risk in regex-based Dockerfile validation for complex multi-stage builds.\n  1039→\n  1040→---\n  1041→\n  1042→## Sprint Completion Summary\n  1043→\n  1044→| Metric | Start of Day | End of Day | Delta |\n  1045→|--------|-------------|------------|-------|\n  1046→| Stories done | 15/20 | 20/20 | +5 |\n  1047→| Epics closed | 2 (0, 0.5) | 5 (0, 0.5, 3, 4, 5) | +3 |\n  1048→| Tests passing | ~2783 | 2872 | +89 |\n  1049→| Coverage-tracked files | 119 | 121 | +2 |\n  1050→| Overall coverage | 96.97% | 96.98% | steady |\n  1051→| Bugs found & fixed | 0 | 17 | +17 |\n  1052→| Tech debt items opened | 0 | 12 | +12 |\n  1053→| Tech debt items resolved | 0 | 0 | 0 |\n  1054→| Releases shipped | 0 | 2 (v0.23.0, v0.23.1) | +2 |\n  1055→\n  1056→**Sprint status: COMPLETE.** All 20 stories done. Next session should prioritize the 3 \"Fix Now\" action items before starting new feature work.\n  1057→\n  1058→---\n  1059→\n  1060→# Session Retrospective — 2026-03-21 (Session 07:51Z–08:12Z)\n  1061→\n  1062→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence Sprint\n  1063→**Session window:** 07:51Z – 08:12Z (~21 minutes)\n  1064→**Sprint progress:** 22/26 stories done (85%), Epic 0 completed, Epic 0.5 at 3/4\n  1065→\n  1066→## 1. Session Summary\n  1067→\n  1068→| Story | Action | Outcome |\n  1069→|-------|--------|---------|\n  1070→| 0-1-sprint-state-live-updates | Docker verification | PASS (4/4 ACs) — fixed migration.ts bug |\n  1071→| 0-2-ralph-progress-display | Docker verification | PASS (4/4 ACs) — fixed proof format |\n  1072→| 0-3-run-command-dashboard | Docker verification | PASS (5/5 ACs) |\n  1073→| 0-5-1-stream-json-claude-driver | Docker verification | PASS (4/4 ACs) |\n  1074→\n  1075→**Epic 0 completed** — all 3 stories verified and marked done.\n  1076→\n  1077→## 2. Issues Analysis\n  1078→\n  1079→### Bugs discovered\n  1080→- **migration.ts missing fields:** `parseRalphStatus()` didn't include new `currentStory`/`currentPhase`/`lastAction`/`acProgress` fields, causing migration test failure. Root cause: Story 0.1 extended the SprintState type but migration wasn't updated to match.\n  1081→\n  1082→### Verification tooling issues\n  1083→- **Proof format sensitivity:** `codeharness verify` requires each AC to have its own `bash` code block — sharing evidence from another AC isn't counted. Verifiers need to know this.\n  1084→- **BATS tests not in container:** `ralph/tests/` directory isn't included in the npm package, so Docker verification can't run BATS tests. This affects all ralph-related stories.\n  1085→- **VictoriaLogs query syntax:** The `_stream_id:*` pattern in the verify prompt template is invalid. Should use `*` wildcard.\n  1086→\n  1087→### Observability gaps\n  1088→- `codeharness progress` CLI emits no structured logs to the observability stack.\n  1089→\n  1090→## 3. What Went Well\n  1091→\n  1092→- **Efficient verification:** 4 stories verified in ~19 minutes. Docker black-box verification is working smoothly for these stories.\n  1093→- **Bug caught:** The migration.ts bug was a real issue that would have caused runtime failures for users upgrading — verification caught it.\n  1094→- **Clean passes:** 3 of 4 stories passed on first verification attempt.\n  1095→\n  1096→## 4. What Went Wrong\n  1097→\n  1098→- Nothing major. The proof format issue for AC3 in story 0-2 was a minor formatting issue, not a real code problem.\n  1099→\n  1100→## 5. Lessons Learned\n  1101→\n  1102→- \"verified\" status in sprint-status.yaml is non-standard — should be `verifying` or `done`. Created ambiguity about what workflow to run.\n  1103→- Verifier subagents need explicit guidance that each AC must have its own `bash` evidence block.\n  1104→\n  1105→## 6. Action Items\n  1106→\n  1107→### Fix now\n  1108→- (none — all issues resolved during session)\n  1109→\n  1110→### Fix soon\n  1111→- Fix VictoriaLogs query syntax in verify-prompt.ts template (`_stream_id:*` → `*`)\n  1112→- Include `ralph/tests/` in npm package or Docker image for ralph story verification\n  1113→- Add structured logging to `codeharness progress` command\n  1114→\n  1115→### Backlog\n  1116→- Standardize \"verified\" status → either `verifying` or `done`\n  1117→\n  1118→---\n  1119→\n  1120→# Session Retrospective — 2026-03-21 (Session 3: Full-day summary)\n  1121→\n  1122→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence Sprint\n  1123→**Session window:** ~05:20Z – ~10:38Z (approx 5 hours across multiple ralph runs)\n  1124→**Sprint progress:** 19/25 stories done (76%), 6 remaining in backlog (Epics 6 & 7)\n  1125→\n  1126→---\n  1127→\n  1128→## 1. Session Summary\n  1129→\n  1130→Today saw three distinct work phases, covering verification of previously-implemented stories and completing two full epics.\n  1131→\n  1132→| Story | Epic | Outcome | Notes |\n  1133→|-------|------|---------|-------|\n  1134→| 4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation | Epic 4: Infrastructure | done | Verified ~09:39Z |\n  1135→| 4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration | Epic 4: Infrastructure | done | Verified ~10:01Z |\n  1136→| 5-1-code-review-observability-check | Epic 5: Workflow Integration | done | Verified ~10:24Z |\n  1137→| 5-2-verification-runtime-integration | Epic 5: Workflow Integration | done | Verified ~11:00Z |\n  1138→| 0-1-sprint-state-live-updates | Epic 0: Live Progress Dashboard | done | Bug found and fixed in migration.ts |\n  1139→| 0-2-ralph-progress-display | Epic 0: Live Progress Dashboard | done | Proof format issue resolved during verify |\n  1140→| 0-3-run-command-dashboard | Epic 0: Live Progress Dashboard | done | Minor format deviations accepted |\n  1141→| 0-5-1-stream-json-claude-driver | Epic 0.5: Stream-JSON | done | Clean verification, no issues |\n  1142→| 0-5-2-stream-event-parser | Epic 0.5: Stream-JSON | done | Required export fix and rebuild |\n  1143→| 0-5-3-ink-terminal-renderer | Epic 0.5: Stream-JSON | done | Completed in final ralph run |\n  1144→| 0-5-4-run-command-integration | Epic 0.5: Stream-JSON | done | Completed in final ralph run |\n  1145→\n  1146→**Result:** 11 stories verified and marked done. Epics 0, 0.5, 4, and 5 all completed. Sprint is now at 19/25 (76%) with remaining 6 stories in backlog epics (6 & 7).\n  1147→\n  1148→---\n  1149→\n  1150→## 2. Issues Analysis\n  1151→\n  1152→### Bugs Discovered During Implementation\n  1153→\n  1154→- **Missing fields in `parseRalphStatus()`** (HIGH) — `migration.ts` did not include `currentStory`, `currentPhase`, `lastAction`, `acProgress` fields added by story 0-1. Returned undefined for these fields. Fixed by adding null defaults to the return object.\n  1155→- **Missing export in `src/index.ts`** (HIGH) — `parseStreamLine` was not re-exported from the package entry point, making it inaccessible when imported from the built dist bundle. Fixed by adding the re-export and rebuilding.\n  1156→\n  1157→### Workarounds Applied (Tech Debt)\n  1158→\n  1159→- **`VITEST=1` env var hack** (MEDIUM) — Container verification of `parseStreamLine` requires setting `VITEST=1` to suppress CLI auto-parse on ESM module import. This is a side effect of the CLI entry point being coupled to module loading.\n  1160→- **`node --input-type=module` for ESM** (LOW) — Container uses this flag to run ESM imports inline. Not a real workaround, but documents a friction point for black-box testing of ESM packages.\n  1161→\n  1162→### Verification Gaps\n  1163→\n  1164→- **VictoriaLogs returned zero events for all CLI invocations** — Affects stories 0-1 (progress command) and 0-5-2 (parseStreamLine). These are pure functions / commands with no structured logging. The observability coverage gap is real.\n  1165→- **No BATS tests available in container** — `ralph/tests/` not included in npm package. Verification of ralph-related stories relied on direct function invocation with mock data instead of the standard BATS test suite.\n  1166→- **Format deviations accepted for 0-3** — Story spec said checkmark/cross prefixes; implementation uses `[OK]`/`[FAIL]` tags. Functionally equivalent but spec-implementation mismatch was waved through.\n  1167→- **Architecture deviation accepted for 0-3** — Story specified `DashboardFormatter` class; implementation uses Ink React components. Same functionality, different design approach. Accepted.\n  1168→\n  1169→### Tooling/Infrastructure Problems\n  1170→\n  1171→- **Non-standard `verified` status in sprint-status.yaml** — Previous session left story 0-5-2 with status `verified` (not a valid state). Had to normalize to `verifying` before proceeding.\n  1172→\n  1173→---\n  1174→\n  1175→## 3. What Went Well\n  1176→\n  1177→- **High throughput:** 11 stories verified and closed in a single day across three ralph sessions. This is the highest single-day throughput in the sprint.\n  1178→- **Two full epics completed:** Epic 0 (Live Progress Dashboard) and Epic 0.5 (Stream-JSON Live Activity Display) both went from in-progress to done.\n  1179→- **Two more epics completed:** Epic 4 (Infrastructure Guidelines) and Epic 5 (Workflow Integration) also closed out today.\n  1180→- **Clean verification on 0-5-1:** Stream-JSON Claude driver passed all 4 ACs with zero issues — demonstrates the implementation quality when specs are precise.\n  1181→- **Bugs found and fixed inline:** Both the migration.ts missing fields and the index.ts missing export were caught during verification and fixed immediately, without needing a separate bug story.\n  1182→- **Session issues log working well:** Every subagent reported issues consistently, providing raw material for this retrospective.\n  1183→\n  1184→---\n  1185→\n  1186→## 4. What Went Wrong\n  1187→\n  1188→- **Observability gaps are systemic:** Two stories (0-1, 0-5-2) had zero VictoriaLogs events because the underlying functions have no telemetry. This is a known gap but it was verified without observability evidence — the AC was effectively waived.\n  1189→- **Spec-implementation mismatches on 0-3:** The story spec described checkmark/cross prefixes and a `DashboardFormatter` class, but the implementation uses `[OK]`/`[FAIL]` tags and Ink components. This was accepted but indicates stories were written before the implementation approach was finalized.\n  1190→- **Export omission on 0-5-2:** A function was implemented but not exported from the package entry point. This would have been caught by an integration test but was only found during black-box container verification. Suggests the build/export checklist is incomplete.\n  1191→- **Sprint status had invalid state:** The `verified` status on 0-5-2 from a previous session is not a recognized state in the workflow. This created confusion about whether to re-verify or just mark done.\n  1192→\n  1193→---\n  1194→\n  1195→## 5. Lessons Learned\n  1196→\n  1197→- **Export checklist needed:** Every new public function must be verified as exported from `src/index.ts`. This should be part of the dev-story or code-review phase, not discovered in verification.\n  1198→- **Specs should be updated when architecture changes:** Story 0-3 specified a class-based design but got Ink components. The story should have been updated to reflect the actual approach before verification.\n  1199→- **Pure functions need observability stubs:** Functions like `parseStreamLine` should at minimum emit a debug-level log or metric, even if they're pure. Otherwise the observability dimension of verification is meaningless.\n  1200→- **Session issues log is high-value:** Having every subagent write to `.session-issues.md` made this retrospective fast and accurate. Keep this pattern.\n  1201→\n  1202→---\n  1203→\n  1204→## 6. Action Items\n  1205→\n  1206→### Fix now\n  1207→- (none — all blocking issues were resolved during session)\n  1208→\n  1209→### Fix soon\n  1210→- Add `parseStreamLine` and `codeharness progress` to structured logging so VictoriaLogs verification is meaningful\n  1211→- Add an export verification step to the dev-story workflow — every new public function must appear in `src/index.ts`\n  1212→- Standardize sprint-status.yaml states: only allow `backlog`, `in-progress`, `verifying`, `done`, `blocked`, `flagged`\n  1213→- Include `ralph/tests/` in the npm package or provide an alternative path for BATS test verification in containers\n  1214→\n  1215→### Backlog\n  1216→- Decouple CLI auto-parse from ESM module loading so `VITEST=1` hack is not needed for container testing\n  1217→- Update story 0-3 spec to reflect Ink component architecture (retroactive doc fix)\n  1218→- Add structured telemetry to all pure utility functions (at minimum debug-level trace)\n  1219→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01WbghDLFsXiBxMyWVBJH7t1","session_id":"14bb9049-f41e-41a8-aff7-919131cd9a0b","uuid":"e4299491-18d8-45c8-8d30-95ac2fe42dbc","timestamp":"2026-03-21T10:41:23.545Z"}
