rials for your retrospective — do not ignore them.\n\nProduce a retrospective that covers:\n1. **Session summary** — which stories were attempted, their outcomes, time spent\n2. **Issues analysis** — categorize and analyze all issues from the session log:\n   - Bugs discovered during implementation or verification\n   - Workarounds applied (tech debt introduced this session)\n   - Code quality concerns raised by reviewers\n   - Verification gaps (escalated ACs, weak evidence)\n   - Tooling/infrastructure problems (sandbox, permissions, CLI issues)\n3. **What went well** — stories completed, bugs fixed, process improvements\n4. **What went wrong** — failures, blockers, stuck stories, wasted iterations\n5. **Lessons learned** — patterns to repeat or avoid\n6. **Action items** — concrete next steps, split into:\n   - Fix now (before next session)\n   - Fix soon (next sprint)\n   - Backlog (track but not urgent)\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-21.md where the date is today.\n\nIf a session retro for today already exists, append to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously.\nDo NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","agentId":"ace34a73233c08696","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Retrospective written to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-21.md` (appended as Session 8).\n\nKey findings:\n\n- **Sprint is effectively complete.** 19/25 stories done (76%), all committed scope finished. Epics 0 through 5 closed. 6 remaining stories are backlog (Epics 6 & 7).\n- **12 stories verified today** across 8 session windows. 17 bugs found and fixed, 75% caught by code review. 2 releases shipped (v0.23.0, v0.23.1).\n- **Critical problem: 12 tech debt items at 0% resolution rate.** The skipped BATS tests have been flagged \"Fix Now\" in 5+ consecutive retros without action